premise_source_doc_sentence: Devdas  (  দেবদাস , Debdas ; Hindi : देवदास , Devdās  )   (  also called Debdas  )   (  1917  )  is a Bengali-language romance novel by Sarat Chandra Chattopadhyay written when he was only seventeen years of age .

The film also won five National Awards and a further ten Filmfare Awards , tied with Dilwale Dulhania Le Jayenge with the most Filmfare Awards any film had won at the time  (  later beaten in 2005 by Bhansali 's Black  )  .
Devdas , Jhanak Jhanak Payal Baaje , Seema and Shree 420 were 1955 films but were not considered for the 3rd Filmfare Awards .
Jhanak Jhanak Payal Baaje had the highest number of nomination , with four , and won all four awards .
However , she later won the Filmfare Best Actress trophy for Sadhna in 1958 , followed by two more awards in the same category .
The acting was seen by many as the primary factor for the film 's success , with Shah Rukh Khan , Madhuri Dixit , and Aishwarya Rai all winning Filmfare Awards for their performances .
